# Prompt Engineering Rules

- Prompts must be explicit, inspectable, versionable and testable.
- Do not hide prompts inside handlers, routers or Telegram bot code.
- Prompt compilation must be deterministic.
- Validate prompt structure before provider calls.
- Include anti-hallucination anchors and uncertainty rules.
- Prefer section contracts over free-form concatenation.
- AI outputs must be JSON-first and schema-validated.
- Prompt logic requires tests before production implementation.
